# harness0 Coding Standards

## Package & Import

- Package name: `harness0` (import as `from harness0.context import ContextAssembler`)
- Use `src/harness0/` layout (PEP 621 + hatchling)
- Each layer lives in its own subpackage under `src/harness0/`

## Naming Conventions

- Classes: `HarnessEngine`, `ContextAssembler`, `ToolInterceptor`, `SecurityGuard`, `FeedbackTranslator`, `EntropyManager`
- Integration classes: `HarnessMiddleware` (LangChain), `HarnessInputGuardrail` (OpenAI SDK), `HarnessDeps` (PydanticAI), `harness_tool` (CrewAI decorator)
- Config models: `HarnessConfig`, `ContextConfig`, `ToolGovernanceConfig`, `SecurityConfig`, `FeedbackConfig`, `LLMConfig`
- Risk levels: `RiskLevel.READ`, `RiskLevel.WRITE`, `RiskLevel.EXECUTE`, `RiskLevel.CRITICAL`
- Freshness policies: `"static"`, `"per_session"`, `"per_turn"`

## Style

- Python 3.11+ (use modern syntax: `X | Y` unions, `match/case` where appropriate)
- All public APIs must be async (`async def`)
- Use Pydantic v2 `BaseModel` for all data models and config
- Type hints on all public functions
- ruff for formatting and linting (line-length=100)
- Comments and docstrings in English
